P1.22 Auto-Scaling Cost Range Implementation Notes:

Implementation completed: 2026-03-29

Changes:
- internal/providers/aws.go:
  - Added MinCount and MaxCount to planInfraInput struct
  - Added costRange struct with MinimumCostMo, MaximumCostMo, Note
  - Added CostRange field to planInfraOutput (populated when maxCount > minCount)
  - Cost calculation: fixedCosts + (perTaskCost * taskCount) for min/max
  - Spending limit check uses max cost when auto-scaling enabled
  - Summary shows range format: '$X.XX–$Y.YY/mo'

- internal/providers/aws_test.go:
  - TestPlanInfra_AutoScalingCostRange: verifies cost range with auto-scaling
  - TestPlanInfra_NoAutoScalingNoCostRange: verifies no range without scaling

Key decisions:
- Cost range only shown when max_count > min_count (auto-scaling actually enabled)
- Fixed costs (ALB, NAT) estimated at $35/mo and not scaled
- Per-task costs scaled by min/max count
- Spending limit checked against max cost to prevent budget surprises

Integration with existing auto-scaling:
- Auto-scaling parameters at deploy time (min_count, max_count) are separate
- Plan-time parameters let users estimate costs before committing
- Plan can specify different scaling than deploy (deploy overrides)
